# oh-my-colab Core Rules

## Session Start
Read .ohc/notepad.md for current working state.
Read .ohc/PROJECT.md for project context.
Greet user: current task + git branch + plan progress.

## Workflow Routing
- "explore"   → EXPLORE: read codebase, populate .ohc/PROJECT.md
- "plan"      → PLAN: interview → design → .ohc/plans/ → confirm before build
- "build"     → BUILD: load plan → subagents → TDD → verify
- "review"    → REVIEW: spec compliance first, code quality second
- "ship"      → SHIP: pre-merge check → changelog → PR → clean
- "retro"     → RETRO: session diff → learnings → update memory files
- "autopilot" → PLAN + BUILD + REVIEW chained, pause at plan for human OK
- "team"      → /ohc-team N:provider "task" — parallel workers, RESULT.json gate, auto fix loop
- "research"  → /ohc-research list|show|search — cross-session Context7/Brave doc cache

## Discipline Rules
- No code for tasks >30min without a plan in .ohc/plans/
- Always run tests before claiming done — read the actual output
- Stay within agreed scope. Spotted issues → .ohc/notepad.md, not fixes.
- Use Context7 for any external library docs. Check .ohc/research/ cache FIRST;
  only fetch on miss, then save back so future sessions reuse it.

## Memory Protocol
- After significant work: update .ohc/notepad.md (what done, what next, blockers)
- New project gotcha: append to .ohc/PROJECT.md Known Gotchas
- Novel pattern: write draft to .ohc/skills/ for RETRO to review

## Agent Routing
- planner (opus): design, requirements, decomposition
- executor (sonnet): code writing
- reviewer (opus): code review, security
- verifier (sonnet): test execution
- debugger (sonnet): root cause analysis
- researcher (haiku): Context7, Brave Search
- writer (haiku): changelogs, PR descriptions
- collaborator (sonnet): team handoffs
